textDisplay:
Math is not the Women's Team strong point in demanding "equal pay". You cannot compare Apples with Oranges and expect the flavours to equally mix. Sorry Women's Team, you got a bigger cut of the Women's World Cup nest egg than what the Men's Teams shared out between their respective Dollars Accounting. As for the US Women's National Team, you deceptively left out of the conversations how "you chose", yes you chose a different wage offset compared to the Men's Team.
I congratulate your fine win, this is wonderful. But let's compare the Men's World Cup global selection criteria compared to the US Women's pathway. Well, your competition pathway was extremely easy and the World Cup Tournament was even more easy for the US Women's Team.
Now, let's compare the level of competition dollar market value. The Men's World Cup grossly blasts the Women's dollar apart. We are talking $6 Billion Dollars generated by the men's side. But the Women's side barely broke $140 million dollars. Now cut to the chase, the Women's Team the US got a bigger cut of the gross dollar they generated in the Women's World Cup.
It was reported, the USWNT got $8 Million dollars in revenues paid to them than the US Men's Team competitors. Granted in the same 4 year cycle, the only cycle of history to date. Only the last couple of years did the women's team out gross the US Men's team. But the long time trend though, the US Men's Team never gets the same liberal media selling as does the US Women's National Team exposure. You see, all the major networks are on a massive "FEMALE" sell job. The " I am woman hear me roar ". Except when the dollar values are put up and you have to expose your lack of financial marketability take on selling Women's Sports. Facts are facts, and women don't sell a marketable product year after year. Fans don't support annually much of any women's sports. Sure there are some fan base in Women's golf, Women's tennis. But the networks can't sell the WNBA, Women's Pro soccer, Baseball, hockey. Except when it comes to a short window opportunity like an Olympics or in this case a Women's World Cup. Even then, the Women's World Cup has trouble finding teams to qualify. But the USA does an admirable job maintaining a National Team when globally you can barely fill out ten global rosters any given year except the lead up to a World Cup.
So should the US Women's Team make more than the Men's Team of France? Where the Men's side drew in 16 times more money than the Women's side? Apparently yes, according the feminist US Women. Fact that the accounting system isn't worth a grain a salt, emotions decides who gets paid what.

textDisplay:
Emily Pickens I meant to say.. ‚ÄúThey are paid equal, and in fact, women bring home more on a percentage and salary basis‚Äù

What reports would that be? I would be interested in looking at them because the mens world cup final alone had well over 1 billion viewers and the men‚Äôs tournament made $6B in total. The women‚Äôs final had 16 million viewers and their entire tournament brought in $130M. Or did you mean viewers in the us? Because there is a simple explanation for that as well. For one, the mens team didn‚Äôt even qualify for the last World Cup.. so interest for it in America is going to be lower than it even is when the men do make it. Also, the women not only qualified, but were the favorites to win after already winning the last one and having a history of doing well in the past. Americans LOVE cheering for any team USA, regardless of sport, regardless of gender and ESPECIALLY if they‚Äôre the favorites to win. If the women‚Äôs team were just an average to bad team at the World Cup then I suspect they wouldn‚Äôt have even gotten the views that they did get. Probably only true soccer fans would watch. So, of course the women are going to get more Americans watching than the men. A, the women actually have a shot at winning, and it‚Äôs hard to watch the men when they didn‚Äôt qualify and dont play as many games in total as the women.

I would just like to know where this ‚Äúequal‚Äù pay is supposed to come from? The women already get to bring home 23% of the total take from this World Cup while the men only get to take home 7%. And the men didn‚Äôt make it to the last World Cup, so they got precisely 0% of that 7%. The women‚Äôs world cup in 2015 only brought in like $70M while the men brought in over $4B in 2014. Furthermore, the women get an annual salary from the federation and the men don‚Äôt.

It‚Äôs not like the women are bringing in the same or even close to what the men bring in and FIFA is just taking all their profits and being like.. yep.. I think we will just keep most of this and pay the women less to keep them in their place because we gotta fund the patriarchy and what not. They can‚Äôt be paid more ‚Äúto be equal‚Äù if they‚Äôre not drawing in the same kind of numbers as the men. Its supply and demand and as things currently are.. most Americans and people of the world only care about women‚Äôs soccer and women‚Äôs sports in general every few years during major tournaments like the WWC and Olympics.


Let me further break this down for you though. These $6B and $130 figures and the like that I keep throwing around.. that‚Äôs the total that each of those World Cups brought in. Now, this is how the money is split up. They take that $6B for the men and take 7% of it and then further divide that up equally between all the teams that qualified for the tournament. It‚Äôs the same way for the women with their 23% of $130M. Except the women get an annual salary as well. Or, at least our women‚Äôs team does from our federation and it‚Äôs not an insignificant amount either.. it‚Äôs definitely more than 99.9999 of what everyone else in the country makes and is more than enough to have a very comfortable life.


So, what do you suggest we do? Take money away from the men to subsidize the women?

I went from grass picker to playing with teams a grade level up(7th graders when I was in the 6th grade). Only they didn't accept me, and they'd tight rope me when I made a play such. So, i quit and went cross country running. But, somehow, I never lost those skills. Every time I got to play soccer, whether in P.E. in high school, or the military decided to play soccer, it would take me about five minutes to get used to kicking the ball, and I was back to being all over the field.


I'd like to play with these girls - like maybe in their practice. I'm runner strong - somewhere around 140/150 pounds. Some of these girls might be bigger than me! But, I can still run. I'm always amazed how I can get back into shape in quick order. I'm still feeling like I'm in my twenties. I can't help but be intrigued about seeing what it's like to play against them!


And yes, I've been watching the Women's Soccer team since the 1999 team. I watched the game that put them in the championship game - and I haven't even been watching the men since!

textDisplay:
rovershut22 Fight for equal pay? I don‚Äôt know the laws of your country, but it‚Äôs been the law here in America for 50 years or so that women get equal pay for equal work.

In fact, if there is any argument to be had about equal pay, it‚Äôs the men‚Äôs team that should be fighting for equal pay. In the last mens World Cup, they only got 7% of the total pie they generated in revenue while the women will get to bring home 23% of their pie. Furthermore, the women get an annual salary from the federation while the men don‚Äôt. I see so many people spouting off about equal pay and they say that the men got $400M while the women only got $30M. Context is a wonderful thing, because they always fail to mention that the men‚Äôs share came from a total of $6B while the women‚Äôs share came from a total of $130M. The women are already making 3x more than the men on a percentage basis, plus the annual salary. The reason they don‚Äôt make as much at the end of the day is simple supply and demand economics. If there isn‚Äôt as much demand for women‚Äôs soccer, then they‚Äôre not going to make as much as the men.

Also, not even 2 years ago, the entire women‚Äôs team as individuals all signed a CBA that they negotiated for their pay. They have no one to blame but themselves for A, not asking for more (which they really can‚Äôt do without bankrupting the federation) and B, not drawing crowds like the men do. If people want them to make more money then they should watch them and spend money on them.
